Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Mix graham crumbs, butter and 1/4 cup of sugar. Press onto bottom of 13x9-inch baking pan. Mix cream cheese, remaining 3/4 cup sugar and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended. Add eggs; mix just until blended. Stir in mashed banana. Pour over crust. Bake 30 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool. Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight. Cut into squares. Top with strawberries, sliced banana and pineapple.